                                <p><strong>WHAT IS ACCREDITATION?</strong><br />
                                <p>
                                    Accreditation is a mandatory process for law firms, stakeholders and potential registrants that wish to act as agents. Accreditation helps to identify a legal practitioner or agent in the area of Industrial Property Registrations<br />
                                </p>
                                <p><strong>BENEFITS OF BEING ACCREDITED</strong></p>
                                <p>       1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Access to the Online filing platform<br />
                                <p>    2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;E-payments with Debit Cards<br />
                                <p>  3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Application Status check<p />
                                <p> 4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Access to fees and Forms<p />
                                <p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Secure filing procedures<p />


                                <p><strong>REQUIREMENTS FOR ACCREDITATION</strong><br />

                                <p>
                                    1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bio Data of Principal Partner (First Name, Surname, Nationality, Date Of Birth, State Of Origin)
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Company information (Name, Address, Email, Phone Number, Contact Person, Contact Number, Date Of Incorporation)
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Account Login Information ( Preferred Username And Password)
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting documents (CAC Certificate, Letter Of Introduction Of Company And Its Representatives, Passport Photograph Of Principal Partner)
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A one-off fee of N23, 500&nbsp; for Corporate institutions and N13, 500&nbsp; for individuals
                                </p>

                                <p><strong>HOW TO APPLY</strong><br /></p>

                                <p>  You can apply online simply by following the steps below</p>
                                <p>
                                <p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Click the get accredited link under the secure member section</p>
                                <p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Read the Instructions and select preferred institution (individual or Corporate)</p>
                                <p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Complete the form displayed and attach supporting documents</p>
                                <p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Take note of your username and password as you would be required to login after submitting your form</p>
                                <p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Click submit and you will receive an automatic email with all the information provided when completing the accreditation</p>
                                <p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Login into your account under the secure member section and click complete accreditation in your user area to generate a successful invoice.</p>
                                <p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Print out invoice and proceed to www.quickteller.com/tpdr to make payment with your debit card or any Skye bank in Nigeria. &nbsp;</p>


                                <p><strong>AFTER YOU APPLY</strong><br /></p>

                                <p>  All applications will be reviewed by the Accreditation Manager. If the Review is successful, you will receive an email confirming your approval. Automatically, your online services links will become active.<p />

                                <p> <strong>AFTER ACCREDITION</strong><br /></p>

                                <p>
